Will Carling and Lewis Moody were among those questioning Wales' decision to keep George North on the pitch against England - despite the winger appearing to be knocked out twice.

North suffered two head injuries during Wales' 21-16 defeat at the Millennium Stadium in the opening match of the 2015 Six Nations on Friday night.

Moody, capped 71 times by England, posted on Twitter: 'Why was George North not taken off - terrible decision by the medics. Out cold.' 

