Moody added: 'Great win for a injury ravaged young england. Jonathan Joseph, George Ford were sublime. Disappointed with medics allowing North to continue.'

Former England skipper Carling also tweeted, saying: 'I really don't think George North should still be on the pitch. He looks very dazed.'

Meanwhile, former Scotland international Rory Lamont - who was capped 29 times by his country - tweeted: 'George North knocked out twice in one game and still on the pitch. How is this still happening?' 

